## Verification Checklist

- [ ] `gblockparty rollback` requires authentication and a linked project
- [ ] Without an argument, fetches recent deployments and shows interactive selection
- [ ] Deployments are filtered to `ready` and `archived` status only
- [ ] Current production deployment is marked as `[current]` and disabled
- [ ] Each deployment shows commit SHA (short), branch, and timestamp
- [ ] With a `[deploymentId]` argument, skips interactive selection
- [ ] Confirmation prompt defaults to No
- [ ] Cancelling prints "Cancelled" and exits with code 0
- [ ] Confirming sends `POST /api/projects/:id/deployments/:did/rollback`
- [ ] Success message includes new deployment ID and URL
- [ ] Failure message includes error details from the API
- [ ] No deployments scenario exits gracefully
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes
